@SCharlesDennicon that's the shitty thing about this. I feel like some of the Buffy cast were happy to be not-so-clear about his real offenses. I feel like some people wanted it to seem darker than it really was.

Whedon was an asshole, sure. There are A LOT of assholes in every industry. I still don't quite understand why being an asshole, even at this level, required the level of black-listing that he received. I do think there are certain people who blew it out of proportion because they were ALSO being an ass (Charisma especially). 

Not saying he didn't deserve something, but it seems insane to me that he's just out. Like he was Weinstein or Epstein.

@bjchit
It is simple. He made The Avengers. That puts him just slightly below God. What makes that we can’t question his actions and decisions.

By now we know that most actors are narcissists, opportunists, world estranged and even worse. The idea of having to work with such people in a world where everybody sticks a knife in you when they get the chance. Nope, no mercy with them.

